definition: to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc
variant of 出[chu1] (classifier for plays or chapters of classical novels)

sentences.english: The arrow went straight and hit the eye of the bird.
sentences.chinese: 箭笔直的飞出去，正中小鸟的那只眼睛。

sentences.english: The thrush flew out as soon as the boy opened the cage.
sentences.chinese: 男孩刚一打开鸟笼，画眉鸟就飞出去了。

sentences.english: Kevin grabbed for his wrist, knocking a sushi roll across the living room.
sentences.chinese: 凯文抓住了他的手腕，一卷寿丝被打的飞出了大厅。

sentences.english: For even as He loves the arrows that flies, so He loves also the bow that is stable.
sentences.chinese: 因为他爱那飞出的箭，一如他爱那安稳的弓。

sentences.english: And from the wood-top calls the crow, through all the gloomy day.
sentences.chinese: 灌木飞出松鸦，乌鸦在树冠上叫唤。

sentences.english: But if you don't need the hands, don't sweat the flying gears.
sentences.chinese: 但是如果你不需要指针，就别鸟那些飞出去的齿轮。

sentences.english: The bird fluttered about, trying to get out of the room.
sentences.chinese: 鸟儿拍打着翅膀飞来飞去，想要飞出屋去。

sentences.english: One empty room next to another after the bees fly out.
sentences.chinese: 蜜蜂都飞出去了，空房间毗邻空房间。

sentences.english: Hails of bottles and bricks were intermittently thrown at police from side streets as reinforcements arrived.
sentences.chinese: 增援的警察到达时从人群中飞出大量的砖头和燃烧瓶。

sentences.english: When he opened the window the bird flew out.
sentences.chinese: 他一打开窗户鸟就飞出去了。

sentences.english: The ravine flew out of sparrow finch.
For even as He loves the arrow that flies.
sentences.chinese: 因为射箭者固然爱那飞出的箭。

sentences.english: Thetruck’s front left tire landed in a rice paddy a football field away.
sentences.chinese: 卡车左前方的轮胎炸得飞出一个足球场那么远。

sentences.english: So let me remind you of what's happening. Satan flies out of hell.
sentences.chinese: 让我来提醒你们发生什么了吧，撒旦飞出了地狱。

sentences.english: Forever as he loves the arrow that flies, so he loves also the bow that is stable.
sentences.chinese: 因为他爱那飞出的箭，也爱了那静止的弓。

definition: be high up in the sky
spout/spray/belch/to well up/to puff out/to spurt out
(not of regular commerce) to sell or dispose of (goods etc)/to get rid of/to unload
(of a meteor etc) to streak across (the sky)/(of a searchlight, lightning etc) to play across (the sky)
to penetrate/to pierce/to see clearly/to have an insight into
silvery light/bright white light/shining white light
